        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 2:02AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 202 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gardner, or near Coal City, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coal City, Braceville, South Wilmington, Braidwood, Godley, East
Brooklyn, Gardner, Diamond, Wilmington, Carbon Hill, Lakewood Shores,
and Channahon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
